    "Traceability:Intro": "Introduction – TraceVerified Traceability System",
    "Traceability:Part1": "TraceVerified Version 2 (TV2) is an upgraded digital traceability system developed to enhance transparency, accountability, and trust throughout supply chains. It provides a reliable digital platform that allows all actors to record, verify, and share product information efficiently and securely.",
    "Traceability:Part2": "The system was developed with the technical consultation of Dr. Heiner Lehr, a European traceability expert, ensuring that TV2 complies with international traceability principles and best practices. Built on the core principle of “one step backward, one step forward,” TV2 enables users to identify where each product comes from, how it was handled, and where it goes next. This ensures full visibility and traceability from production to consumption.",
    "Traceability:Part3": "Developed by TraceVerified, TV2 meets the growing demand for digital traceability solutions that align with global food safety and sustainability standards. It supports organizations in strengthening consumer confidence, ensuring responsible supply chain management, and building a more transparent business ecosystem.",
    
